            <div class="pageContent">
                <h2 class="title">Don’t Miss the Excitement…</h2>
                <strong>The 2009 TopCoder Open includes:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Algorithm Competition Semifinal and Final Round</li>
                    <li>Marathon Competition Finals</li>
                    <li>Mod Dash Competition: Three Quick Final Rounds</li>
                    <li>Studio Design Competition: Two Final Rounds</li>
                </ul>
                Read more information about the TCO09 competitions <a href="http://www.topcoder.com/tco09" target="_blank">here</a>.
            </div>
            <div class="pageContent">
                <h2 class="title">Don’t Miss the Innovative Discussions…</h2>
                <strong>In addition to the great competitions, we are also featuring the following Discussion Forums:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>TopCoder Q & A, Featuring Jack Hughes, Founder and TopCoder staff. </strong>  This round table discussion will be an opportunity for TCO09 attendees to ask questions and start conversations with the Founder of TopCoder, Jack Hughes as well as other TopCoder personnel.  It will be an open discussion that will also be available to members online.</li>
                </ul>
          <ul>
                    <li><a href="http://sensations.aol.com/" target="_blank">AOL/TopCoder Sensations Developer Challenge</a>, <strong>featuring Tom Wlodkowski, Director, Accessibility at AOL.</strong>  The discussion will summarize the competition, the accessibility applications built throughout, and showcase the big winners.</li>
                </ul>
                <em>More Innovative Discussions to be announced soon!</em><br/><br/>
                <strong>We will also feature three competition round tables that will go into more detail about the application building process for the AOL/TopCoder Sensations Developer Challenge:</strong>
          <ul>
                    <li><strong>Specification and Conceptualization</strong>: After accessibility experts chose 6 ideas from more than 160 submissions, the Conceptualization and Specification process investigated each idea in much greater detail.  This panel will discuss the road from idea to production-ready requirements.</li>
                    <li><strong>Architecture and Assembly</strong>: Once the projects were defined, architecture provided the technical plan for realizing the Sensations Developer Challenge applications.  This panel will discuss the project’s architectural plan and its realization during assembly.</li>
                    <li><strong>Components</strong>: Componentized code is core to TopCoder’s production methodology.  This panel will explore a few of the components produced during the Sensations Developer Challenge.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
